    <name>
      <text>8.3.5 (Does limit exist limit from recurrence relation)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Suppose that a sequence is defined by the recurrence relation 
\[
u_{n+1} = {@aa@}u_n + {@bb@}.
\]
What is the limit of the sequence? if you believe the limit does not exist type in <code>none</code></p>
<p>Limit=[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Recall that a sequence given by a recurrence relation \(u_{n+1} = {@aa@}u_n + {@bb@}\) has a limit if \(-1 < a < 1\). In this case \(a = {@aa@}\) so a limit exists and therefore the limit is given by 
\[
L = \frac{b}{1-a} = \frac{{@bb@}}{1-{@aa@}} = {@ta1@}.
\]</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
